A4.text: The Japanese manufacturer Suzuki has used the Baleno nameplate since 1996.

A5.text: The Baleno nameplate was discontinued in Europe and Asia-Pacific after 2001.

A6.text: The Baleno nameplate was a rebadged Cultus Crescent from 1996 to 2002.

A7.text: The Baleno was produced and sold in India as the Maruti Suzuki Baleno until 2007.

A9.text: The Vitara continued production under the name Escudo in Japan.

A10.text: Suzuki produced the Vitara model in Hungary starting in 2015.
